Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.89,0:00:03.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ladies and gentlemen,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.96,0:00:07.02,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I bring you marvelous illusions that \Nmake this town sparkle at night!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.02,0:00:11.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Tonight, I hope you enjoy the miracle \Nof a ruby that guides someone's life.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.44,0:00:18.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Kid the Phantom Thief has issued \Nanother declaration of war!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.81,0:00:23.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This time, his target is the world's largest ruby,\N owned by the Hopper Magic Troupe.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.49,0:00:28.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sheesh. That sneak thief will never learn, \Nno matter how many times he's foiled.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.21,0:00:31.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Dummy. I return 'em on purpose!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.84,0:00:34.50,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,'Cause they're not the jewel I'm after.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.50,0:00:36.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You shouldn't do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.18,0:00:39.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A-Akako?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.46,0:00:40.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Shouldn't do what?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.18,0:00:43.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm talking to Kid the Phantom Thief.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.18,0:00:50.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That ruby is called a demon stone because \Nmisfortune comes to anyone who tries to get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.51,0:00:52.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Red Tear...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.65,0:00:57.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But if Kid insists, then it can't be helped.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.21,0:01:00.42,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Red Tear?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.42,0:01:03.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, that jewel is the one...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.94,0:01:06.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A long time ago, Dad...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.33,0:02:51.48,Signs - Thief Title,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(500,0)}Red Tear
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.89,0:02:51.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector Nakamori! Kid the Phantom Thief \Nsent out another advance notice!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.48,0:02:52.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.94,0:02:56.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We already got his advance notice yesterday!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.84,0:03:01.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He said he's going to steal the world's \Nlargest ruby from the Hopper Magic Troupe
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.45,0:03:05.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,during their dinner show at \Nthe Minato Hotel tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.09,0:03:07.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But this came today...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.50,0:03:11.50,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.50,0:03:13.46,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,To My Dear Inspector Nakamori,\NDisregard what I said in yesterday's notice... \NPlease excuse my absence.\N- Kid the Phantom Thief
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.46,0:03:15.92,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He's calling it off?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.12,0:03:20.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, did you see the news this morning?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.99,0:03:23.02,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Nope.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.20,0:03:25.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Here, this.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.63,0:03:28.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,"Kid the Phantom Thief \NConcedes an Early Defeat!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.51,0:03:31.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Is He on the Verge of Retiring?!"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.28,0:03:35.36,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sheesh. I oughta sue for libel...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.80,0:03:40.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,"Jody Hopper, leader of the \NHopper Magic Troupe, comments:
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.06,0:03:44.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,"It's a shame I won't get \Nto see his magic." Huh...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.86,0:03:48.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He must be scared of Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.40,0:03:50.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He's a coward when it comes down to it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.34,0:03:53.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Jackass! Who could be afraid \Nof that third-rate inspector?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.47,0:03:57.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I have a good reason for \Nnot stealing that jewel!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.13,0:04:02.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He just picked Aoko's pocket!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.01,0:04:03.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.88,0:04:04.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.10,0:04:12.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, what's wrong? Kaito?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.30,0:04:15.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.09,0:04:18.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This is yours, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.09,0:04:22.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.96,0:04:25.72,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Th-Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.72,0:04:27.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,In that instant,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.53,0:04:29.95,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,she got Aoko's wallet back!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.95,0:04:33.50,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And so fast, it made the first pickpocket \Nlook as subtle as a freight train!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.19,0:04:37.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Who is she?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.87,0:04:42.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Honestly. I heard the Japanese let pacifism \Nlull them into a sense of false security,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.05,0:04:44.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,but I didn't think it was this bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.61,0:04:50.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you the leader of \Nthe Hopper Magic Troupe,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.52,0:04:52.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Jody Hopper-san?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.74,0:04:53.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.69,0:04:56.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, she's a magician...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.06,0:04:58.02,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No wonder she's got fast hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.70,0:05:01.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Remember, Kaito, she's in \Nthe news site's article...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.98,0:05:04.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.05,0:05:07.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Her grandfather is James Hopper,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.81,0:05:10.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,once the greatest magician in England!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.60,0:05:13.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.04,0:05:17.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,His father is Kuroba Toichi, \Nonce the greatest magician in Japan!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.93,0:05:19.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Idiot. It's {\i1}the world...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.69,0:05:21.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. I know of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.42,0:05:27.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The world's foremost illusionist, \Nknown as the Magician of East Asia.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.98,0:05:33.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But in the end, he and my grandfather \Nwere both like that pickpocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.58,0:05:39.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Just cunning swindlers who deceived people \Nand rolled them for their money.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.94,0:05:44.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,B-But you do magic, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.56,0:05:49.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,After my grandfather died two years ago, \NI had no choice but to inherit the troupe.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.18,0:05:51.36,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But even so, this is it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.56,0:05:53.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.09,0:05:56.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Tonight is the \NHopper Magic Troupe's last show.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.22,0:05:59.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Both of you, come and see it if you'd like.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.30,0:06:02.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If you care to be tricked
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.77,0:06:04.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,by swindlers like us.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.44,0:06:11.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's them!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.97,0:06:16.35,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The mysterious organization that \Nmurdered Dad eight years ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.21,0:06:19.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So they're after it, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.93,0:06:22.42,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The Red Tear that Jody-san owns!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.28,0:06:27.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Their objective is to obtain Pandora, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.90,0:06:31.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No way are they gonna pass up \Nthe world's largest ruby.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.39,0:06:34.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And after I canceled the \Nadvance notice for Dad's sake...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.13,0:06:39.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, what are you muttering \Nto yourself about?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.39,0:06:41.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The movie's gonna start!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.47,0:06:47.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Two people at the hotel entrance,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.87,0:06:51.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,one in the revolving restaurant on the roof,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.28,0:06:52.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,and...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.89,0:06:55.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...three here at the dinner show.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.93,0:07:01.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I've got detectives in the audience too, \Nbut... is he really not gonna show?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.90,0:07:03.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Jeez...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.52,0:07:06.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you look so serious, Dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.36,0:07:09.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Kid's not coming tonight, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.86,0:07:12.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So you should enjoy this!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.80,0:07:15.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yeah, you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.46,0:07:18.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Amazing! Amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.44,0:07:22.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, boy. Kaito was supposed \Nto come with me...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.23,0:07:27.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No way am I gonna see a show put on \Nby people who disrespect magicians!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.77,0:07:29.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And so here I am...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.74,0:07:33.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,How does the venue look?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.77,0:07:37.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There are three or four \Nplainclothes cops in the audience.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.06,0:07:40.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But we don't see anybody who could be Kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.06,0:07:42.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, just as planned.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.80,0:07:45.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Execute the plan in ten minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.98,0:07:47.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And don't screw up.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.66,0:07:48.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.82,0:08:21.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, Paul...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.12,0:08:23.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Nice job.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.69,0:08:25.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,When did you get this good?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.62,0:08:30.36,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Probably because it's his last chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.11,0:08:33.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not just Paul.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.54,0:08:37.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The others are also going all out
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.32,0:08:40.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,to improve their skills.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.44,0:08:44.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They want you to keep \Nthis magic troupe going.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.75,0:08:46.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I already told you, Robert.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.21,0:08:53.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,When I took over, I gave you all two years \Nto find real jobs, and that's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.56,0:08:57.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If you want to keep the troupe going,\N you can do it yourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.30,0:08:59.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,B-But...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.18,0:09:02.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...you're the only one who \Ncan keep us together...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.28,0:09:08.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sick of being in this world \Nof lies and deceit.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.82,0:09:12.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides... I want this to be the last time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.17,0:09:16.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The last time I wear this accursed jewel...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.95,0:09:23.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,M-My lady...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.04,0:09:26.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Look!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.30,0:09:30.13,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the leader, Jody-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.73,0:09:34.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then that's the world's biggest ruby, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.22,0:09:37.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Just a moment!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.82,0:09:39.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you with the troupe?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.93,0:09:41.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.08,0:09:44.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Does she always wear that jewel?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.28,0:09:45.42,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.42,0:09:49.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's basically the trademark \Nof our magic troupe.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.49,0:09:55.10,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, I didn't see Jody-san listed \Nas a performer in the program...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.10,0:09:57.95,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Is she not very good at magic?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.29,0:09:59.95,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Heavens, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.95,0:10:02.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ever since my lady was a little girl,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.53,0:10:07.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,her parents and grandfather, \NJames-san, taught her,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.66,0:10:11.02,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,so even now, she's the most talented \Nmagician in the whole troupe.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.24,0:10:14.42,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So her parents perform magic, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.78,0:10:17.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.21,0:10:20.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They were a brilliant pair \Nin the world of magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.34,0:10:24.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Until they died ten years ago, \Nin an accident in the middle of a show.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.82,0:10:32.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That was the day James-sama was going to \Nretire and pass the jewel on to those two.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.64,0:10:49.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ever since then...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.77,0:10:54.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...my lady has felt disdain for magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.28,0:11:02.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And since then, that ruby has been called \Na demon stone, bringer of misfortune.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.36,0:11:06.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, Akako-chan \Nwas saying something like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.72,0:11:09.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Jody-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.09,0:11:14.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And now, for our finale, the Human Cannon!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.08,0:11:30.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,How about letting me...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.14,0:11:33.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...take care of the show's finale?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.69,0:11:37.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,K-Kid the Phantom Thief!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.17,0:11:41.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't let him get away! After him!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.55,0:11:42.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.50,0:11:49.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What? He sent a note saying he wasn't coming!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.82,0:11:52.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You just can't trust a thief!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.92,0:11:55.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Kid the Phantom Thief...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.93,0:11:58.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Paul, take our lady to the dressing room!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.16,0:11:59.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,R-Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.16,0:12:05.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Relax.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.96,0:12:08.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We haven't killed anyone yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.41,0:12:11.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to count to three.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.32,0:12:15.88,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't want to get hurt,\N give me that jewel.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.86,0:12:18.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't do it, my lady!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.84,0:12:20.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,One!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.62,0:12:21.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Robert!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.73,0:12:22.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Two.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.58,0:12:25.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Three!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.21,0:12:32.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,P-Paul!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.20,0:12:38.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Moron.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.12,0:12:39.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, give it here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.90,0:12:43.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Unless you want to join him...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.57,0:12:50.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Halt, Kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.32,0:13:03.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,K-Kid shot at me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.42,0:13:07.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It can't be...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.38,0:13:11.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, give it to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.22,0:13:13.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You can have...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.60,0:13:16.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...this jewel!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.93,0:13:22.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You mustn't, my lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.37,0:13:25.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't give them the jewel.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.62,0:13:27.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,P-Paul!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.69,0:13:29.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you all right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.15,0:13:32.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. I'm wearing a bulletproof vest.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.38,0:13:34.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,B-Bulletproof vest?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.81,0:13:36.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would you have that?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.15,0:13:40.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's because...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.61,0:13:48.13,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...I'm really Kid the Phantom Thief!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.99,0:13:50.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.15,0:13:52.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But Kid was out there...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.81,0:13:55.50,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That was probably one of their accomplices.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.50,0:13:59.31,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A decoy to lure Inspector Nakamori and \Nthe other officers out of the venue.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.79,0:14:01.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then what about Paul?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.34,0:14:04.26,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He's been on the toilet \Nsince before the show.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.11,0:14:10.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No wonder! I didn't think Paul \Nwas up to that level of magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.22,0:14:14.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This Red Tear is your target, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.76,0:14:18.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But I didn't think you were coming \Nafter you canceled the advance notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.58,0:14:21.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't come here to steal that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.96,0:14:25.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I came here to protect...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.12,0:14:27.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...both you and the jewel.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.71,0:14:35.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.29,0:14:39.13,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They escaped upstairs?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.97,0:14:41.31,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll go after him!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.80,0:14:43.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You guys get lost!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.23,0:14:43.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.68,0:14:49.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,All right! Just a little more!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.71,0:14:56.02,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn you, Kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.08,0:14:59.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That fraudulent bastard...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.96,0:15:04.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're not going anywhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.61,0:15:07.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit! All right, try this on...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.10,0:15:22.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what you get!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.82,0:15:26.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,She's not James Hopper's \Ngranddaughter for nothing...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.59,0:15:27.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Bitch!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.55,0:15:35.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, tell me...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.56,0:15:39.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you want to protect me and the jewel?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.85,0:15:41.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Answer me, Kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.08,0:15:45.04,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Minato Hotel\NRevolving Restaurant
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.82,0:15:58.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You've got nowhere left to run.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.86,0:16:02.89,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, give me that jewel.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.84,0:16:09.89,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Her jewel isn't Pandora.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.91,0:16:14.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, you're the one \Nwho has nowhere to run.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.97,0:16:16.03,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.40,0:16:31.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I-It's spinning!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.22,0:16:33.92,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I did a little tinkering
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.92,0:16:36.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,with this restaurant's revolving mechanism.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.85,0:16:49.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,B-Bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.84,0:16:58.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And right as our guest is arriving!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.58,0:16:59.71,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.71,0:17:01.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,S-Snake-sama!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.90,0:17:22.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Kid. You saved me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.39,0:17:27.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But "Demon Stone" fits.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.00,0:17:30.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Because of this jewel, \Nmembers of the troupe were injured
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.24,0:17:33.07,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,and the show was ruined...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.42,0:17:38.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This really was the last performance \Nof the Hopper Magic Troupe.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.86,0:17:43.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,With apologies to my grandfather, \Nit looks like I can finally be free.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.24,0:17:48.03,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Free from the world of magic that \Nrobbed my parents of their lives...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.03,0:17:50.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And free from this cursed ruby, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.29,0:17:54.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I know how you feel.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.85,0:17:57.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But magic doesn't kill people.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.78,0:18:01.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The jewel will tell you that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.62,0:18:04.50,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you think it's strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.68,0:18:09.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Normally, rubies are red, \Nbut that jewel is blue.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.82,0:18:12.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And its name is "Red Tear."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.69,0:18:15.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,N-Now that you mention it...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.52,0:18:19.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Red, a key word used to describe fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.91,0:18:24.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Observe.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.19,0:18:33.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Your grandfather, James Hopper,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.35,0:18:36.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,left this to your world, his final...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.14,0:18:40.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...magic trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.12,0:18:45.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,G-Grandfather...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.60,0:18:48.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Papa... Mama...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.94,0:18:53.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And me, when I was little...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.06,0:19:04.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A letter?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.89,0:19:08.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,"My darling Jody..."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.36,0:19:11.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You may despise magic
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.89,0:19:16.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,for killing your parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.03,0:19:22.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I just want you to recall once more
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.76,0:19:27.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,the rush of excitement \Nyou felt when performing
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.97,0:19:29.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,on stage the first time...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.76,0:19:33.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And the enthusiastic applause.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.08,0:19:39.36,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,When this jewel glows red,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.22,0:19:47.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I pray that Jody Hopper, magic's gift \Nto the world, shall rise again.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.40,0:19:51.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,James Hopper.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.62,0:19:58.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,G-Grandfather...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.46,0:20:03.92,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.35,0:20:11.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He uses the jewel's refractive index \Nto make the glow of flames appear.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.93,0:20:13.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's projection magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.93,0:20:17.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh! Wow, he's great!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.05,0:20:19.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,To make a device like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.28,0:20:23.26,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. He calls it "Red Tear."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.60,0:20:28.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,My magic mentor inserted it \Ninto the jewel for his granddaughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.69,0:20:30.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's very special magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.36,0:20:35.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I protected it,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.58,0:20:36.92,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.46,0:20:42.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Both of my parents \Nwere so proud of my magic...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.08,0:20:46.26,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd completely forgotten.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.84,0:20:51.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So you used to look like that \Nwhen performing magic, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.01,0:20:55.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to give it one more shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.57,0:20:57.95,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Magic...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.26,0:20:59.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...and the magic troupe, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.62,0:21:08.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaito!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.28,0:21:13.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's this? You were curious \Nand came after all, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.40,0:21:17.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Pfft! I can do whatever they can!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.01,0:21:19.92,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then do it right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.24,0:21:23.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Dummy. I'm done with tricks for the night.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.17,0:21:28.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,After the Red Tear, anything \NI did would pale in comparison.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.22,0:21:32.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Kaito!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.73,0:21:35.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sheesh! You're so stubborn!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.41,0:21:45.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A miracle called the Red Tear.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.81,0:21:51.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Making that magic work requires the device, \Nknowing the trick, and one more thing...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.14,0:21:53.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Love embedded in the jewel.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.18,0:21:58.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, see you next illusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.41,0:23:32.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaito! Let's do the preview together!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.52,0:23:34.03,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you want?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.03,0:23:37.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm here to help you! The last \Npreview I did was popular!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.47,0:23:39.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What do I care about popularity?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.08,0:23:42.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,In the next episode, a mysterious \Nphantom thief in black appears.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.41,0:23:43.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It sounds like he has a duel with Kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.80,0:23:46.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna win... No, I mean,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.08,0:23:47.02,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Kid's gonna win!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.02,0:23:49.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time on {\i1}Magic Kaito 1412{\i0}:
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.02,0:23:52.91,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Midnight Crow (Part One): \NThe Name is Corbeau the Phantom Thief!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.78,0:23:52.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,"Midnight Crow (Part One): \NThe Name is Corbeau the Phantom Thief!"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.44,0:23:56.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Step right this way. Watch carefully!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.41,0:23:58.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't miss the illusion.
